"ATitle: the fake protector by Alex-the-Amazing at All poetry
"
"ê	You left me alone and cold world to take care of myself so you could feel no pain and worry, you had me be the mother when I was the child and now you want to punish me for that. &nbsp;Well now you can leave since now I don't need you, If only you could understand the anger and pain I feel inside. &nbsp;To burst with tears every night and feel all hope is lost, while you shake in with-drawl in the next room. To be alone in a cruel world without a protector makes me cold inside, to know that my protector should be you when you can only think of yourself. So now I've learned to protect myself, and you made my walls high and now nobody can break them down. Not even I, no matter how much it hurts me, I can't let it come crashing down now.
