"5Title: nonsense by ArcticIllusion at All poetry
"
"„	<p class="i">Surrounded by broken glass, a facade of smiles and reflections of what&nbsp;my&nbsp;mask should look like. The vomit stains on this&nbsp;dress will never come out&nbsp;and my soul will never be clean. Bitemarks and bloodstains cloud so many weakened hearts. and the shadows never leave. so many times I wished it were me up on that pedestal, when the weight of my insecurties crashed through the stone, falling to the floor like cigarette ashes floating through your hair and the alcohol swimming in your eyes. i wish i could take it away. make you see how your killing yourself. but i've tried and failed. like i always do. </p>
"M<p class="i">I can do everything you would ever ask of me, except love you the way you want, hold you the way you've been dreaming of for so many years. I cannot kiss away your tears because I'm afriad of tasting the mascara running down your cheeks. Your are mine, and mine alone. A butterfly that died in its cage, like the swarm of honeybees that were trapped in your hair. We made believe everything would be fine as long we remained staring in each others eyes. As long as out fingers&nbsp;intertwined, time would stop long enough for us to see this isnt how it was meant to be. </p>
".<p class="i">I could scream your lies right out of the sky and tear down your wall of smoke rings that are making me choke up mistakes i've long since forgotten. just fold me up neatly, pack me in your suitcase and forget me til the next time you need to run away from your many false reflections.</p>
"End of Poem
