"4Title: Only Me by ArcticIllusion at All poetry
"
"¿	All the houses sit where they landed. Dropped from the sky in pretty rows of perfect houses. Each and everyone of them the same but in different colors. This one blue, that one white.<br />
"<br />
"aI run past them so fast my sneakers never touch the ground, never touch the puddles that fill &nbsp;the spaces in the sidewalks as the rain comes down faster then I can run. Washing away the color of everything, falling like those houses fell so long ago that no one remembers they dont belong here. That they weren't always the way they are now.<br />
"<br />
"(I don't belong here either, with the houses all made in the same shapes..each and every one filled with stories and sad eyes like mine. Each of them with towering maple trees to soak up the sun and the rain so that people inside forget there is a world outside that doesn't belong to them.<br />
"<br />
"uI don't think I belong with these pretty houses on their perfect curving streets named after famous dead people, because I am not pretty nor perfect. I am only me, Samara Rayne Michaels. I'm not anyone else and never will be. Everyone pretends they are someone else, everyone tells me I can be anything I want to be. But I know that's not true I can never not be me.<br />
"<br />
" That's how I know I don't belong here, that I belong up there...where the houses fell from, up where the stars are drawn in like pencil marks on the sky.<br />
"<br />
"áI wouldn't have to run to get there. It wouldnt be easier then running, be easier then closing my eyes and never opening them again. Maybe even as easy as a wish.."If I die before I wake I hope I don't come back the same"..wishing every night but I know wishes dont come true because I'm not as little and dumb as I used to be. I know that if you throw a penny in a fountian it just sits and rusts there, that if you wish on a star, its a waste of thinking, a waste of hope.<br />
"<br />
"ÑI run under the powers lines above my head and wonder when the rain will seep through the rubber and onto the wires..sending electricity sparks through the treetops like fireworks as I run under them with my socks wet through my sneakers. All the faces pressed up in their windows to watch me running, rain rolling down my face and maybe i would smile for them and they wouldn't smile back because they might be scared to see me running in the electric rain.<br />
"<br />
"$Only that never happens.<br />
"<br />
"End of Poem
