"Author: BestDeceptions 
"5Title: Learning by BestDeceptions at All poetry
"
"	<br />
"­Today’s children should be taught to live in the moment. Instead, they are trained to want success and happy endings. It becomes so easy to forget to enjoy the ride. <br />
"<br />
"âMe, I’ve always been a beginner. I live for the start of new seasons and I thrive in the midst of fresh starts. I hate endings – their finality is deadly – hallmarks of forgotten memories, expired loves, lost feelings. <br />
"<br />
"S“But you can’t live your life in fear,” he said to me the other night. <br />
"<br />
"‰“I’m not,” I replied defensively. “I’m only being cautious. I’ve learned this the hard way. I just don’t want to get hurt again.” <br />
"<br />
""He stared back at me. <br />
"<br />
"ç“You know what your problem is?” he asked softly. “You overthink everything. You can’t control the world, sweetheart, no matter how hard you try. Sometimes you’ve gotta throw caution to the wind, live without looking back.” <br />
"<br />
"¶“That’s what scares me,” I whispered through the beginnings of tears. “I’m afraid that when we’re over, you’ll never look back. I can’t stand the thought of being forgotten.” <br />
"<br />
"@He took my hand and looked me straight in the eyes. <br />
"<br />
"c“We haven’t even had the chance to begin yet. Why are you already writing our ending?" <br />
"<br />
"–It made sense. I’d never thought about it before, but my tendency at the beginning of anything is to first look to the ending. But why? I swear, someone should have taught me sooner to be happy with what I have. To live for the sake of being alive. Maybe if they’d instilled in me from the start a sense of satisfaction, instead of always pushing me to do better, to aim higher, to gain more – maybe I could live with contentment. Maybe I could live without doubt, and insecurity, and fear. Oh, if only they had taught me to believe… I could be like him, a dreamer, living without looking back. And more importantly, without always having to look forward.<br />
"<br />
"<br />
"End of Poem
