"6Title: Temporary by BestDeceptions at All poetry
"
"0	Billy tells me this is only temporary; he says it won’t be long before we’re together again. &nbsp;I don’t know if I believe him or not, but whenever I tell him that, Billy gets a strain in his voice and he gets mad that I’m doubting him. &nbsp;Whenever I cry, I can tell that it scares him, and he gets real serious and he shuts everything else out and concentrates on trying to make me stop, and this is what makes me think that maybe, maybe, just maybe he really does love me the way he says he does. &nbsp;But then the next day, Billy doesn’t call.<br />
"<br />
"÷The problem is that he still wants to act like everything’s the same, and I just can’t get over the fact that it’s not. &nbsp;He says he still loves me, that I should know how much he cares about me, that he still wants us to be together, and that why would I think this has something to do with some other girl? &nbsp;He’s with ME. &nbsp;But that’s the problem, he’s not with me anymore, and it was all his own choice. &nbsp;Billy broke up with me, it was five days after our anniversary. &nbsp;<br />
"<br />
"ÿHe says it’s because of his parents. &nbsp;Billy says that he’s just going through a lot of personal stuff right now, and that he just needs some time to deal with things on his own. &nbsp;He says that if we’re together right now, his parents will hate me, because somehow I’ll get involved in the argument. &nbsp;Billy doesn’t want his parents to hate me, so that’s why now we’re just friends. &nbsp;I say that I can’t see why it matters whether or not his parents like me, if we’re not together anyhow.<br />
"<br />
"
I tell him that I just don’t understand it; he says he’s already explained it the best he can. &nbsp;I say I just need to talk to him about it, I have questions, and I just need him to try to answer them the best he can. &nbsp;He says okay, but then we never do and whenever we start to, just when we’re finally starting to get somewhere, we get interrupted and we can’t finish it. &nbsp;I tell Billy that he’s just not the same anymore, that he’s different now, it feels like he doesn’t want to talk to me, and like he’s trying to avoid seeing me. &nbsp;He says he feels like I don’t want to talk to him anymore, because whenever we’re on the phone, I don’t have anything to say. &nbsp;I say that’s not it, it’s just that I can’t tell anymore how he really feels. &nbsp;<br />
"<br />
"`I tell Billy that I used to think I had him figured out, but that I sure can’t tell anything anymore. &nbsp;Billy laughs; he says that’s real cute that I ever thought I had him figured out. &nbsp;I like it when Billy tells me that I’m cute, or when he calls me by one of his pet names, or uses one of our inside jokes. &nbsp;The other night we were on the phone, and he got real quiet and all he said was “You’re ridiculous, kid,” and I could hear everything he was feeling in his voice, I could feel his eyes closing shut, and I could feel his breathing getting shorter. &nbsp;See, that’s what Billy used to tell me when we’d kiss. &nbsp;We’d be in the backseat of his car, having one of our ‘conversations,’ and after a few minutes, he’d pull me close and close his eyes and just sigh. &nbsp;“You’re ridiculous, kid.” &nbsp;And then he’d kiss my forehead.<br />
"<br />
"2I miss the nights like those with Billy, and I try to tell him that. &nbsp;It’s the times like those that make me think Billy really does love me. &nbsp;I tell Billy that I don’t want to be his friend. &nbsp;He pretends to get offended, and says “well, fine.” &nbsp;But I’m real strong, and I don’t let his feelings get to me. &nbsp;I just keep a straight face and I say “You know what I mean,” and I don’t let anybody crack me. &nbsp;Billy knows exactly why I don’t want to be his friend. &nbsp;He knows I want to be much, much more than just his friend.<br />
"<br />
"-And last night, Billy told me that he doesn’t want to just be my “friend.” &nbsp;He tells me that this won’t be long, that this is only temporary. &nbsp;He says it doesn’t have anything to do with any other girl, but I still don’t know if I believe him. &nbsp;But then again, I can’t blame him because I flirt, too. &nbsp;That’s how me and Billy met, we’re both big flirts and we flirted together. &nbsp;Lots. &nbsp;I used to think I’d never forgive any man for thinking about any other girl but me, that if he so much as looked at another girl, I’d leave him. &nbsp;After all, if he was with me, I should be the only girl he needs or wants to talk about and think about. &nbsp;But now, I’m not so sure, because Billy has pictures of calendar girls in his room, and there are girls at work that flirt with Billy all the time, even though they know about me. &nbsp;And it bothers me, and it hurts, and I hate to have to watch it, but then again, at the end of the day, Billy IS with me. &nbsp;I mean, that’s gotta stand for something. &nbsp;It just has to. &nbsp;<br />
"<br />
"¿I don’t know where me and Billy are going next, and I don’t know where we’ll end up, because I can hardly even remember where we’ve been. &nbsp;I don’t know if I care either, so long as we end up somewhere together. &nbsp;I’m still so scared to trust Billy, and I just don’t know if I should let it out or not. &nbsp;But even through all of this, I know I still love him, because I just can’t get him off my mind. &nbsp;I feel safe with him, even when I’m scared, just like I am now. &nbsp;But right now I gotta go. &nbsp;Because I’ve been trying to get a hold of him all night, after all the crying I did on the phone with him last night, I just need to talk so bad. &nbsp;And Billy just called.<br />
"<br />
"<br />
"<br />
"End of Poem
