":Title: Rights for ALL!! by Cadee Blaze at All poetry
"
"ù	They live among us, work in the same jobs, and have friends and family just like the rest of society. &nbsp;There is just one little difference that tends to bother people. &nbsp;These people are still different; they are homosexuals. &nbsp;<br />
"mReligion states that they are sinful and do not deserve the rights such as heterosexuals, but in today’s society who is not sinful? &nbsp;People are experiencing intercourse before they are married; adultery is committed yet no one thinks anything of it. &nbsp;The Bible even states that getting a tattoo is sinful. &nbsp;How many people have tattoos? &nbsp;<br />
"%	Just recently have things begun to change but part of that is due to the War on Terrorism. &nbsp;Under the Presidency of Bill Clinton the Don’t Ask, Don’t Tell policy was put in place, so gays and lesbians could fight for the county they love just as heterosexuals are aloud to. &nbsp;<br />
"	The military and armed forces are the leading employer for the United States. &nbsp;They set an example for the rest of the businesses, if the military will not higher people based on who they take to bed then why would other businesses have to. &nbsp;These people wish to sever their country; they are citizens just like everyone else. &nbsp;What happened to civil liberties? <br />
"	What I don’t get is why people are so afraid of them? &nbsp;Or wish to kill them? &nbsp;They bleed just like other people do, laugh and cry just like other people do but they have a different sexual orientation so there must be something wrong. &nbsp;Other countries allow homosexuals in the military, such as England and Canada. &nbsp;Most countries even have rights to protect homosexuals. &nbsp;The U.S. News wrote an article about rights for gays in Canada and in Ireland. &nbsp;Why hasn’t the United States done anything about it?<br />
"G	Isn’t the United States based on freedoms and rights for all? &nbsp;So why are homosexuals so different? &nbsp;Gays and Lesbians are not mutated humans, aliens, or mental patients, yet our country and most of the citizens treat them no better. &nbsp;Is it because people always seem to fear what they do not understand?<br />
"	"When I was in the military they gave me a medal for killing two men and a discharge for loving one." This was taken from the tombstone of a gay Vietnam veteran. &nbsp;People are comfortable with killing but not when a man loves a man or when a woman loves another woman. &nbsp;<br />
"Þ	If the only reason for people disliking homosexuals is religion then we should go back to the old ways. &nbsp;Meaning, women who cheat on their partner must be stoned and children must be beaten as their punishment. &nbsp;Other things have progressed over time and I hope that the rights for homosexuals will improve as well. &nbsp;I just want to know when the hate and witch hunts will end. &nbsp;Maybe my children and their children will be safe from bigotry and hate.<br />
"End of Poem
