"7Title: The Teddy Bear by Co-Co-Cola at All poetry
"
" 	Remember me, Jenny? &nbsp;Of course not, you must be nearly a teenager by now. &nbsp;But don't worry, I remember you. &nbsp;Oh yes . . . I remember you.<br />
" &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;"I'll always love you" "You'll always be my best friend" "I'm glad I can tell you everything."<br />
"O &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;No cognizance? &nbsp;Not even a little?<br />
"␀ &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Oh well, that's alright. &nbsp;I didn't expect you to bring alive such vivid memories of innocence. &nbsp;Remember that word? &nbsp;Innocence? &nbsp;Of course not. &nbsp;It's a nonexistent purity that was once my battery.<br />
"M &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Oh but that was a long time ago . . .<br />
" &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;For ages, I was that cuddly, little something you held in your arms when you were frightened, sad, or just needed something to snuggle in those nippy nights. &nbsp;You loved me. &nbsp;I loved you. &nbsp;My nectareous, marveling obsessions for you were welcome as you embraced me in your childlike, undeveloped bosoms. &nbsp;A paedomorphic corruption, on my part.<br />
"	<br />
"3 &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Until . . .<br />
"	<br />
"Ì &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;You came home one day. &nbsp;That beastly, repugnant day. &nbsp;Someone else resting in you hand. &nbsp;Another girl. &nbsp;Her bags were flung at my side of the bed, where we would sleep peacefully and you would calmly whisper into my stuffed ear "Good night." &nbsp;Your nails were drawn over. &nbsp;Your hair was fondled with. &nbsp;Your lips . . .oh . . . how they were tainted horribly with a calm red saturation. &nbsp;<br />
"– &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;She called you beautiful now. &nbsp;But you were much beautiful before your acrylic disguise of your lovely flaws. <br />
"	<br />
"F &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;You were beautiful to me . . .<br />
"	<br />
"} &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;You left me crying under the bed, where you hid me from all your new-found friends. &nbsp;<br />
"C &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Were you embarrassed of me?<br />
"Ç &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;I guess you're just like all the other children that would once be found playing and laughing with their teddy bears that now leave those cherished memories behind.<br />
"G &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Why would you want to leave me?<br />
"+ &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Me?<br />
"A &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;I made your memories fun.<br />
": &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;I looked over you.<br />
"Q &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;I listened when no one dared give an ear.<br />
" &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;I helped get rid of the monster under the bed and those nightmares that would leave you crying. &nbsp;Being there for you was everything I had. &nbsp;I didn't even mind being punched into when you were storming with rage. &nbsp;<br />
"	<br />
"¸ &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Ah, but my power was concealed inside this obsidian, fluff-stuffed body. &nbsp;My marble eyes hid the ability. &nbsp;The talent. &nbsp;The gift . . .<br />
"	<br />
"€ &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Who do you think created those nightmares? &nbsp;Who else would know your fears more than me?<br />
" &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;You were my toy. &nbsp;To play with. &nbsp;To manipulate. &nbsp;I pried at your mind--I stuffed it with nightmares, just as my body was stuffed with rich cotton. &nbsp;I licked at your heart, tasted it's black tar. &nbsp;Your black locks, how much fun I had with those. &nbsp;Remember that dream? &nbsp;When you dreamt your hair was being pulled out by a horrible black monster?<br />
"F &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Guess what? &nbsp;It was . . .<br />
"	<br />
"A &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Your tears were my honey.<br />
"| &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Your skin was my cutting board, as I butchered you with my distinct, adorable nails.<br />
"I &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;I gave birth to your frustration.<br />
"u &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Time may pass by, but I am that persistent demon that clutches to your dress.<br />
"	<br />
"ä &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;No one knows of me. &nbsp;I float through the world as a ghost, forever unnoticed. &nbsp;No one has even seen my powers. &nbsp;But you, Jenny, you are a victim of them. &nbsp;You are my puppet.<br />
"	<br />
"( &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<br />
"<br />
"<br />
"<br />
"C &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;I will use you, Jenny . . .<br />
"	<br />
"( &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<br />
"<br />
"<br />
"( &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<br />
"<br />
"<br />
"< &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;To become real . . .<br />
"<br />
"<br />
"<br />
"<br />
"<br />
"<br />
"<br />
"<br />
"<br />
"<br />
