"5Title: Freeverse1 by Day Old Hate at All poetry
"
"?	My eyes open as the sun breaks through the window onto my face. As my eyes open, I remember what you said, and realize that the only bliss that I was feeling, was the beautiful dream that I was having. When I wake, all of the feelings of panic, hurt, depression, and fear, suddenly come rushing back to me and hit me like a load of bricks. I feel as if nothing matters anymore, and if I commit suicide at this exact moment, no one would care, or even notice that I was gone. Not even you. And you said that you loved me. You promised. But not everything that everyone says is exactly how they feel, even if that is what they thin that they feel at the time. How do you know that this is true? Have you even showed me? Have you even tried to be close to me? Those are my immediate thoughts as soon as I wake in the morning. <br />
"<br />
"ÅI stand up, and look at my face in the mirror. I hate what I see. I hate the way my hair flows across my face, down past my shoulders. I hate how my blue eyes begin to tear. I hate how I feel so low all of the time, and mostly because of you. I wonder if one day I will not feel this way anymore. Like all of this will just fade away, and I will be better again, with nothing to fear, and no reason to want to die every waking moment of my life. <br />
"<br />
"aWhen I finally put on my face, and realize that this is a new day, my eyes wont stop tearing. I hurt more and more, and I hate it. I think about you. I want to be with you every second of my life, but at the same time, I want you to die. I remember everything that you’ve done to me, and everything that everything that you said that hurt me. All of the abuse that you threw upon me, and how horrible you made me feel, by everything that you said, just killed me every time I thought about it. I want to forget about this, and just move on, but sometimes the pain gets too strong, and I can’t hold on to the thought of forgetting you. You meant more to me than anyone in my entire life, and I wish I didn’t feel this way about you still, after all of this time, and after everything that you did to me. You made me hate myself, because you loved me so much. <br />
"End of Poem
