".Title: Bad Taste by Elly A at All poetry
"
")	Dark hours of my misery return to run a lap with the minutes on the clock. I refuse to be a mannequin on display for you to fashion with abuse. Guilt has never been my favorite accessory and my sensitivity can't stand the chipped crystals embedded by my cries. I'm full of reasons to despise your name, yet I long for your change and most of all your happiness. When the time comes and you cross into another state of being, I pray you find the glory you so much want. Hell is what you've been living, and in your eyes I was only an addition to that turmoil. Tell anyone who approaches you that your bitter scent is the perfume of my memory. I won't defend myself, your anger is stronger than this hand of mine reaching out to help you. So place the blame on me, paint my pain with the color of your choice and cover your back with it. Let my suffering be the blanket you hide under and my tears be the warmth you bathe in. Continue lingering in our miscommunication while I smile here and think of why I loved you in the first place. Nothing can change that you were the soul with the laughter and hope that pushed me to that so called stage of happiness when nobody else was there. You can't help how you feel and there's nothing I can do to keep from being the bad taste left in the mouth of where your emotions mix.
"End of Poem
