":Title: Response to Judgement by Elly A at All poetry
"
"«	Quick to defend that of which is yours, don't you see that words do not have to be spoken to be felt? They don't have to speak aloud and say what they really think it can be heard miles away through simple small actions. Whether spoken or felt don't you see that the pain remains the same? You which have not been judged do not know the feeling but those who have know my heartache. If setting your own beliefs, following and standing up for them is wrong then label me a bad influence. If my actions don't fall in that of which is "normal" be it my cutting, my anxiety, my insomniatic moments..then label me a freak. If sharing my feelings open and honest beyond that of which you dislike, I do not apologize for the way I am but I apologize for the offense to your close minded character. Do not tell me i am not being judged when the feeling is so much there for if you do not want me to feel that way let your actions show otherwise.
"End of Poem
"8Title: Insomniatic moments by Elly A at All poetry
"
"	<br />
"çAt night paranoia sets in the feeling of eyes staring at me comes into play...I was never able to adjust to the ticking of the clock or the branches hitting the window the things that go bump in the night are the things that make my skin crawl...When everyone sleeps I sit here staring at the pictures of a man that brings me joy...To see those pictures is to feel as if he's still here with me and that is the only reason I am able to not feel so alone. Sleep to others such a simple task to me the most difficult...I live in an opposite world I sleep by day and live by night. I become so in tune with myself listening to the beating of my heart...the thoughts and memories swirling my mind the trembling of my hands as my anxiety slowly sets in. My salvation is getting too tired to stand straight I tire myself out at night to the point where I have no choice but to throw myself on the bed and sleep. God help my soul as it fights sleep one more time give me peace as I await tonights slumber.
"End of Poem
"0Title: Confessions by Elly A at All poetry
"
"	<br />
"?Inside I'm hurting something I or words can't express, my cutting...it's a confession I keep hidden a confession I will not confess. my soul used to be filled with brightness, color, and light...now it's replaced by darkness, dullness, and night. My heart has been broken..a scar that will not heal. I look in the mirror seeking my reflection but what is this I see? The one staring back at me is not me...daily I am overcome by sadness and anxiety whether it be seconds, minutes, hours, or the entire day..these are the feelings that are yet to go away. I question if others can see the amount of pain hidden behind my eyes, or is it invisible to those I trust? Questions questions...Why? What am I living for? What must I learn? What lesson is God teaching me? So many goals but which one must I accomplish?....Time is against me, but I will strive to win. I must stand up to my fears...Will I have enough courage when it's right? Will I be able to let go? I need encouragement, I need motivation from those who care because the pain sometimes I fear will one day be too much to bare.
"End of Poem
