">Title: A Decaying Sanctuary by Eros Ikhnos at All poetry
"
"!	A Decaying Sanctuary<br />
"<br />
"=Splotches of rain fall upon my archaic sanctuary.<br />
"1A desolate gray lay upon the heavens,<br />
"0Hovering overtop my sweet hide away.<br />
"7Decaying walls on my once beautiful refuge.<br />
"3Take away the grandeur at once it rest.<br />
"6Volley after volley of unwavering attacks,<br />
".Leaves my inner fortress breached.<br />
"*Clouded and dazed one becomes,<br />
"2When his only resting place is seized.<br />
