"KTitle: [.Vows of enternal love.] by FullchamberRoulette at All poetry
"
"(	Today, We are gathered here to witness these two people proclaim their undying love to one another. &nbsp;With these rings, they promise to become one, from this day forth. &nbsp;To never love another, to be each others backbone, To love through sickness and in health, when poor or rich.<br />
"~We are here, to not judge, but view them as one. &nbsp;Two people to share their life's until their lasts breaths.<br />
"<br />
"+With this ring I give to thee, <br />
",I promise to love you undyingly.<br />
"&You are my life, my breath<br />
"&I am yours, till my death.<br />
"#I promise to do my part<br />
"'You complete my black heart<br />
"3With this ring, I proclaim you my wife.<br />
"0You're my everything I want in life.<br />
"<br />
",I place this ring on your finger<br />
"-And with these words I will utter<br />
"&I love you, more than life<br />
"-I give myself to you as your wife<br />
" The ring is a symbol<br />
"+Of our love that is so mirthful<br />
"$I take you as my husband<br />
".And of this love that was destined<br />
"!You are my everything<br />
"#Forever Until My ending<br />
"<br />
"‚Will you take this man as your husband, in happiness and with patience and understanding, through conflict and tranquility?<br />
"<br />
"With you take this woman as your wife, in happiness and with patience and understanding, through conflict and tranquility?<br />
"<br />
"¢In years to come, Caring is not always easy. &nbsp;It is easy to give up. &nbsp;We hope that your love is eternal, threw ever problem we hope you overcome.<br />
"ZIn this hope, may they keep the vows made on this day, in freedom, teaching each other who they are, what they yet shall be, enabling them to know that, in the fullness of being, they are more than themselves and more than each other, that they are all of us, and that together we share joyously the fruits of life on this earth, our home.<br />
"<br />
"MI now pronounce you, for the first time As one, Husband and Wife.<br />
"<br />
"4You may now claim what is yours. You may kiss.
"End of Poem
