"3Title: Sex? by HopelessRomantic at All poetry
"
"{	what is so wrong with sex? why is it frowned upon in our society? what is so wrong with pre-marital sex? i talked to my ex last night...we're talking about getting back together. we dated for a year and a half...the whole time talking about going all the way...giving each other our virginity...it never happened. then when we're talking about getting back together...when im hitting on her, she comes out and says that she's waiting for marriage. i felt betrayed...i felt lied to...but why? theres nothing wrong with wanting to wait until marriage. what is sex after all? surely its nothing more than a mating process thats been around since mammals evolved (or were created...depending on your beliefs). why did i feel so horrible when she told me she was waiting? why did she decide to wait? there are so many unanswered questions about the topic. ive thought for a long time that its something you do with someone when you love them enough...but lately ive been wondering. maybe its a drive given to us by hormones...the hormone that influences the want to reproduce. maybe its not about fun at all...ive always had a feeling that human beings are nothing more than poorly tended machines...and this may just be how we're programed. i cant say for sure...but sex seems like an awfully touchy subject to be looked upon so simply like most people do (IE its something special thats for that one person...or its just a fun thing to do with another person). i dont believe that its so simple...but ive never thought about it enough to be conclusive. maybe this deserves a few hours of solid thinking...and i'll continue this when i've done said thinking... 
"End of Poem
