"QTitle: Just...Thoughts. Venting, I Guess. by Immortally Yours at All poetry
"
"X	So....currently, I am with Someone-Who-Loves-Me. (And I always will be...) <br />
"_I say 'with'. because I'm not necessarily 'without'...but he's not here, "with" me.<br />
"Confusing enough.<br />
"Can you handle it?<br />
"<br />
"NI am...confused. I don't really know what I'm doing here, exactly.<br />
"tBy 'here' I don't mean...here where I am sitting, but...my purpose to be. My existence in its entirety. <br />
"eSee...if I was in Texas, with that Someone-Who-Loves-Me, maybe I wouldn't be so confused.<br />
"_Maybe, just maybe, I'd actually feel like I actually belong somewhere, to someone. <br />
"ðEven the mother of that Someone-Who-Loves-Me likes me more than my own other does, apparently. Mine isn't showing to have that much of a positive impact on my life. Which...if it was me...I wouldn't think it to be such a good thing. <br />
"cMy mother doesn't seem to care all that much; it doesn't really bother her at all. Meh.<br />
"„So...if anyone feels like they want to...pitch for me to go and live in Texas, just let me know. T'would be much appreciated.<br />
"‹It's weird, not that many people from Canada feel like the only place they might belong is in Texas...that's pretty much unheard of.<br />
"‹Ist of all, it's an American state...(no offence), and this is Canada. 2nd, ...it's Texas of all states(again, no offence intended).<br />
"íIt isn't necessarily me wanting to go to Texas for the sake of it being Texas, it's that that Someone-Who-Loves-Me-That-I-Can't-Live-Without just happens to live there. In another country. At the very bottom of that other country.<br />
"Convenient, no?<br />
"No.<br />
"Not at all.<br />
"2It makes my life a bloody living Hell.<br />
"zThe worst part is, I don't think I've ever really loved somebody as much as I love that Someone-Who-Loves-Me. <br />
"=If I even knew what love was before I met Him... <br />
"tAnd he's so fucking far away...so far away, that he's in a different effing timezone. I'm an hour ahead.<br />
"Lovely.<br />
"ŸOh yeah, and his mom actually likes me, wants to by me a plane ticket just so I could go over there. And, apparently, I don't even have to go back home.<br />
"LI don't think I'll ever be able to get a chance like that again.<br />
"<br />
"By the way....<br />
"2I've never met him, or his mom before.<br />
"#Did I forget to mention that?
"End of Poem
