"DTitle: What I Love About You by Immortally Yours at All poetry
"
"&	What do I love about you?<br />
")Well, there are many things. <br />
"%I love the way you are...<br />
"%Meaning, the overall you.<br />
"6The way you talk, the sound of your voice.<br />
"¿How deep it is..and the way it goes deeper when you try to be serious [not that I don't take you seriously<img src="http://img.allpoetry.com/images/smile/tongue.gif" /> ], and the way it goes slightly higher when you know you're arguing a failing point and you know I'm right....or when I embarrass you, and you don't know what to say.[though...that really is quite cute of you.<img src="http://img.allpoetry.com/images/smile/roll.gif" /> ]<br />
"I love the way you're so pretty and handsome....with your pretty blue-ish green-ish eyes, and pretty pink lips...and the way you smile with them and though I don't see it...I can hear it...even though you don't think I can hear somebody smiling over the phone.<br />
"ZI love the way you beg for random things...even if there's nothing to beg for, and I remain totally clueless as to what you want. I love the way the word 'please' just rolls off your tongue in that one way that makes me melt and give in, then beg for you to stop begging for whatever it is you're begging for...even if it's nothing at all.<br />
"—I love the way you like provoking arguments just for the sake of arguing with me, and then remaining totally speechless most of the time when I 'win' the 'argument', because you know I'm right.[<img src="http://img.allpoetry.com/images/smile/happy.gif" /> ]...and because I flatter you too much and you don't know what to respond with.[<img src="http://img.allpoetry.com/images/smile/tongue.gif" /> ]<br />
"¤I love the way you contradict me whenever I say something bad about myself, then make me feel better and happier. And then I always manage to smile or laugh.<br />
"ÕI love the way that whenever I think about you, and the way you talk...a smile just seems to appear on my face and I start to daydream about you...and me with you...and everything about you and me with you.<br />
"%I love the way you always seem to say something that leaves me at a loss for words...or I stutter and my voice goes higher and funny, and you tell me to calm down when there was nothing to calm down for...I was just overrun by your charm, and nervous about making a fool out of myself. <br />
"¾I love the way you tell me that I don't need to be nervous, worried, shy, or that I don't need to say sorry when I'm talking to you, and then you ask me why I am, and I say 'I dunno'.<br />
"I love the way I ask you a question, and you answer my question with another question, leaving me speechless once again.<br />
"±I love the way we have so much in common, yet we can't really find anything to talk about...and then there's total silence, in which case you always say 'hello' to check if I'm still there, though I'd never leave you. [<img src="http://img.allpoetry.com/images/smile/happy.gif" /> ]...and that in turn makes me smile for some odd reason. I don't mind all the silence...I get to listen to you breathing when it's quiet. I'm sorry if that sounds creepy, but as I said, I love everything about you. Even your breathing. Your breathing and heartbeat are two things I'd like to listen to all the time...and two things that could put me to sleep with happy dreams, and a smile on my face.<br />
"»You're awesome, amazing...and virtually indescribable [in a good way<img src="http://img.allpoetry.com/images/smile/happy.gif" /> ], and not a thing in the world could change that.<br />
"^I love you my Lil Teddy Bear<img src="http://img.allpoetry.com/images/smile/rose.gif" />
"End of Poem
