"NTitle: Borrowed Heart, Never Returned by IronyIsADeadScene at All poetry
"
":	Tears of pain and anguish roll down her cheeks <br />So many years ending in heartbreak <br />All she could do was blame herself <br />They had made so many foolish mistakes <br />All the things he promised leaving her in gasping breaths <br />Her happiness leaving her in his back pocket <br />Drowning out her pain in her tears <br />She planned to burn the notes, and the pictures <br />Leave the memories as ash <br />Letting them be whisked away to dance on the wind <br />She clung tightly to what was left of herself <br />Her sanity <br />Without him she doesn't know who she is <br />She always thought she wasn't anything without him <br />Now she felt like a nothing <br />Was she anything to him at all <br />They had plans <br />They had so much more to experience <br />She wanted to tell him she loved him <br />And she didn't want this <br />Before he left she gave back his shirt that she always wore <br />She gave the necklace and a desperate smile <br />But as she watched him walk away <br />All she could do is whisper <br />You forgot to give my heart back.
"End of Poem
