"<br />
"ìWhat is real? Real is a house, a home, a family, a life. That is YOUR real. That is MY lie. The lie that you tell the little girl so that she will stop <em>crying</em>, the lie you tell her when you say everything is <em>ok</em>. Well its <b>not</b>. It¡¯s <b>NOT OK</b>. It¡¯s a <em>lie</em>. <em>Life</em> is a lie, a harsh lie where you are told that you are ¡°living¡± and if you are lucky, lucky and pure of heart, you will continue to live this lie, this lie of life. But if you sin, you little sinner, you will be told the TRUTH. The truth about real. Real: the demon that chains me to this living hell, Real: the swamp at the end of the road; sticky and black. Real: the dark creature that haunts me in my dreams¡¦the only place I though it was safe, the only place I could hide. Real is when you realize that you are not loved, real is when you realize you <em>have never</em> and <em>will never</em> be loved. Real is when you realize love is a <b>lie</b>; real is when you realize there is <b>no love</b>. Love is what you told the little girl to make her stop crying. You told her you loved her. But you <b>don¡¯t</b>. You don¡¯t love her-->she cries. Crying is a sin. EVERYTHING is a sin. YOU are a sinner, a sinner punishable in hell, the hell that is real. And you wonder¡¦.why do I <em>cry</em>? What have I done so <em>horrible</em>? What was my <em>sin</em>? You were <b>smart</b>. You pondered, you doubted, you explored, you searched for something <u>other than these lies</u>. There was something about them that was <em>not real</em>. And <u>you found it</u>. You found out the <b>secret</b>. They told you there were no secrets. They <b>lied</b>. But if they lie than what Is the truth? The truth is you beat the system, you broke their lie. Everyone was too fucking afraid to do what you have just done. Now mommy <em>hates you</em>. Daddy <em>HATES YOU</em>. They¡¯ve always known, know that you are <b>special</b>, you are <b>different</b>, you are <b>smart</b>. They had hoped that they could <em>keep you quiet</em>. They could <em>hide you forever</em>. &nbsp;They could fill you with lies like their parents had done to them. They could make you like <u>all the other children</u>. They could tell you they loved you. Maybe that will make you stop <em>crying</em>, stop <em>sinning</em>, maybe that will make you fit in. Maybe you wont break free, maybe you wont be smart, maybe if they lie to you they can <b>keep their own lies</b>. Their <em>lying way of life</em>. They <b>fear</b> you. They <b>fear</b> the change. They <b>fear</b> the TRUTH. They always told you the truth was bad. The truth had sin. The truth is for sinners. You are an <em>outcast</em>, so they <em>cast you out</em>. You are too much of a <b>threat</b>. A threat to the life of their lie, their LIE OF LIFE. They <u>must</u> cast you out. They <u>must</u> punish you. You are to face REAL. You are shown the door, you are stripped of your clothes, stripped of your lies- the lies you now wish you could have held onto. <em>Why</em> did you have to be so smart? <em>Why</em> were you so special? <em>Why</em>? <em>WHY?!</em> &nbsp;Now you are cast, thrown, kicked into these firey pits of real. You drown in these fires <em>so cold</em> that you freeze, but you were already frozen, you were always frozen. Frozen and cold. WAIT. This is not freezing you are feeling -it is thawing-, you are felling it for the first time, you are felling EVERYTHING; ANYTHING for the first time. This new warmth overcomes you. Like a wave of <b>life</b>. And you realize that these are not fires, but waves, with every stroke: every motion it brings you a better sense of real, and real life. And the way things really should be. The ice breaks, it melts away, your heart takes it¡¯s first REAL beats, your lungs take their first REAL breaths, you mind has its first REAL thoughts. This real air is dense, it is heavy, but at the same time it puts a slight smile on your face, your <em>first REAL smile</em>. And you KNOW that it is real. Unlike life, real is not a lie, it does not deceive, it does not tell the little girl to shut up, she is not told to stop crying. Real embraces her with open arms. She no longer has to hold it in, no longer lets it collect like ice, no longer it builds up multiplying, enumerating, adding on into thicker sheets and masses of ice and depression to carry on her shoulders. So she embraces the real as it embraces her. She lets it all out. She is so relieved. She hesitates, she should not have told her secrets, she should not have expressed how she really felt. She has sinned. Real shall surely scold her, hit her, cast her out just like the others. She awaits her punishment, she dreads to think what is in store for her, she has done it again! Why must she be like this? But Real does not scold her. Real does not judge her. Real lets her be the real human being that she is to be. So give real a chance. Embrace the life that should be real. A life that ought to be real. But life is still a lie, and no one wants to <em>embrace</em> Real. No one wants to <em>reach</em> for something more. They like their lies. Well you know what? It is too late for them. They are caught up in their <b>own lies</b>. Well fuck them. Mommy <b>lied</b>. Daddy <b>lied</b>. They are <u>part of the lie</u>, <em>embracing the lie</em>, unwilling to <u>reach out for real</u>. <em>Go ahead</em>. I <b>don¡¯t</b> care. Fuck you, you lied. You are a lie, you¡¯ve always been a lie. I just never saw it. You are not real. You are no realer then the lies you told me. Goodbye. I don¡¯t need you. <br />
".Its too late. Too late for all of you. But its not too late for us. We are the generation of hope. No &nbsp;longer will they push us around, no longer will they push us aside, no longer will they tell us the lie, no longer will they deceive us with their words. No longer will they keep us in the dark. Come with me to the light. A place where you can be REAL, experience everything that should be real. Come with me, follow my example, be smart, break the lie, abolish the hate! Crash through the surface! Gasp for air! Come now, Hold my hand. Together we charge the walls of hate- we trample them and leave them in the dust. Maybe if we succeed they will be left as only a lie. Come with me: run, jump, dive into the seemingly flames of real. Dive deep and realize that they are in fact waves, currents of ups and downs, good and bad, hope and wisdom. Embrace the ever beating of your heart, the thumping of your very soul. Lets challenge these lies, take in knowledge, learn, think, lets <em>take on</em> these waters, <em>swim</em> these currents, <em>sail</em> these seas. Together lets take these ¡°lies¡±, these lies of happiness and love, bring them with you to real. Bring them here, <em>hold onto them tight</em>, lets make them <b>real</b>. Realer then they ever were. Lets take these falsities and make them into something <em>better</em>. Lets start a new life. Lets start over. Lets make things <b>right</b>. This starts with <b>you</b> and <b>me</b>. Lets take the ideas I thought were lies, lets take love, laughter and happiness, Lets make them <b>REAL</b>. <br />
"<br />
"End of Poem
