"	*I Stand Alone.*<br />
"<br />
"$\Part one: the darkness\<br />
"<br />
"<br />
"5I am awakened, I find myself in the dark.<br />
"KWhat is this place? It seems familiar, have I been here before?<br />
""Here in this darkness?<br />
"I stand alone.<br />
"NThere is nothing here, nothing but feelings of sadness and hatred,<br />
"YJealousy and betrayal, a storm of black forms above my head in this darkness,<br />
"DAnd it rains tiny raindrops of or pain and despair, and,<br />
"I stand alone.<br />
"+The acid rain of hate rains and<br />
"-Pours onto my bare shoulders with<br />
"5The weight of a thousand nightmares, and <br />
"I stand alone.<br />
"'My umbrella has broken, and<br />
"GThe acid rain burns me and drains my life of any happiness,<br />
")As I wrinkle in the rain, and<br />
"I stand alone.<br />
"!The puddle at my feet<br />
" rises and grows,<br />
"4It has reached my ankles, I am cold, and<br />
"I stand alone.<br />
".I close my eyes and try to see my <br />
"JDream I was awoken from, I try to feel the warmth of my dream,<br />
">But all I feel is cold, I open my eyes, and still,<br />
"I stand alone.<br />
"BI look down; the puddle of black has reached my waist.<br />
"$The cold is taking over.<br />
"5I will surely drown in this darkness, and<br />
"I die alone.<br />
"%There must be something, <br />
",Someone who can help me get out,<br />
":I look around- no one, only darkness, because,<br />
"I stand alone.<br />
"EI must get out! There must be more to life than darkness!<br />
"?Where is the light? I seek it! I search my pockets,<br />
"FBut I find nothing, for I am naked, naked in the dark, and<br />
"I stand alone.<br />
"(The puddle is swallowing me.<br />
"3The black and terror rises to my chest.<br />
"OWith every icy breath I take, I scream. But there is no answer, for<br />
"I am alone.<br />
")Its horror creeps up my neck,<br />
":My breath becomes slow, and the cold takes me.<br />
"OEvery inch of my being quivers and shakes with fear and terror. And<br />
"I stand alone.<br />
"I am dieing.<br />
"4I close my eyes for I no longer want to <br />
"3Stare into the darkness any longer, and<br />
"I stand alone.<br />
"0The puddle of black reaches my chin,<br />
"2I open my mouth to call out once more,<br />
"!But it is no use, for<br />
"I stand alone.<br />
"*The dark floods into my mouth,<br />
"6And down my throat, into my lungs, its ice<br />
"GAnd hatred is more that I can take, but no one can save me-<br />
"I stand alone.<br />
"*My nose, my eyes, my forehead,<br />
"'The puddle has engulfed me.<br />
"<I have drowned and I am nearly frozen and still,<br />
"I stand alone.<br />
"*My heart takes its last pumps,<br />
"8I think about how it wasn’t always this way,<br />
"MAnd a faint smile spreads across my face as I remember happiness-<br />
"6Before it is stolen by the darkness, where<br />
"I stand alone.<br />
"(Frozen and limp I have died,<br />
"%Here in this darkness and<br />
"!I will never be free.<br />
"I die alone. <br />
"<br />
"'\Part two: A new beginning\<br />
"<br />
"2Suddenly, the faintest speck of light,<br />
"@Your hand plunges into the darkness brining me hope-<br />
