"<Title: lonely sunset by LET x ME x BLEED at All poetry
"
"2	So this is it. The climax of this sweet fairy tale, the peak of one dying romance. The point in which the sunset touches the ocean, where heaven meets earth. Your warm lips caress my neck like the gentle kiss of the ocean breeze. And like a wave of hope washing over me; my heart thumps and beats endlessly for you, and I forget all my problems as I close my eyes and take it all in. And for one mere second, my world is at peace, and everything is okay. But in an instant, just as quickly as it came, my sense of love and security is carried away by the summer winds. And I realize that it is not you that I felt, well maybe it used to be you, but now it is just another playful wisp of memory blowing in the wind and forever taunting with my heart. I open my eyes and I see that I stand alone in this sunset, alone for you are no longer beside me. Now there is only one. One of us; an us that no longer exists. Only one pair of sandy feet, only one softly spoken lullaby to the sea, only one lost lover, and one broken heart. There is only one, one because you are gone.
"End of Poem
