"Ã	He awoke in a cold sweat. Demes and emotions swirling though his head like fire. “Their watching” came a voice from the darkness. He turned in fright eyes wafting from past lack of sleep <br />
"k“ wh-where..” he choaked thought dry and barren.. There was a pause. “Where?” he called into the darkness body shaking with the electric fear. “Their watching...” it called again sound slithering from the very depths of night..“ wh-what do they want?” His sintes tangled with alertness eyes seeing though the dark midnight ink and scooping out the depths of his room. “ where..where are they?” again no answer came but a simple whisper, soft and sinister, “ &nbsp;their watching..” there was a movement in the corner of his eye he turned holding bake a scream as the dart of depth slipped away out of his sight. <br />
"<br />
"Ø &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; He stayed rooted to his bed in till there was a knock upon his door as it was pushed slowly opened revealing his dishevel mother, robe hastily raped around her well formed body, angry look cluttering her otherwise china doll face. “What is it this time Kiyel ?” she yawned loudly, “ I though boys your age hade grown out of this kind of things…..” she trailed off giving him a look of mirth and bore. He swallowed a hasty get out. He did not want his mother off all people in here right now of all times, not when he was so close to finding out. “Nothing mother. It was just…. A night mare that all.” He lied lamely clinching his bed &nbsp;sheets tightly in his hands. Once again she smirked “ah yes I see. A nightmare right, ok thin good night Kiyel” she turned and shut his door without waiting for a returned ‘goodnight’ or ‘I love you’ He sighed heavily and spared a glance once more around his room. He knew there would be no more sleep tonight. The clock flashed 3:28 in bloody red letters, he yawned lightly and clicked the light on quietly slipping on to muffed carpeted floor, and crossing the room to his closet for close, it was going to be another long day.<br />
"<br />
"– &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;“Mr.Kiyel” there was an impatient rap on his desk and he jerked violently out of his thoughts.<br />
"ß “Ah Mr.Kiyel so nice of you to join us,” his teacher smirked behind her glasses, murmured giggles slipped thought the class, “ I hope I didn’t disturb any thing important with my teaching did I?” He looked up into her eyes placing a bored look upon his face. “ actually Miss. Donor I was hoping you would halt the lesson for me whale I finish up this thought “ he turned bake to the window and gazed out absently totally ignoring the fact that half the class hade ether gone dead silent or was cracking up at him and the teacher who hade now gone three shades of red and still turning hade ordered silent and stomped bake up to the bored to finish her lecture on Latin America. “She’s a bit to smart for that one” he complained to himself half wishing the stupid one’s where the ones he got instead of his friends. All he needed was the pass room and some quiet. With her rambling on about forgery contrary he couldn’t concentrate. He sighed and shut his book as the last bell rang for dismissal. Another long day of narrowly avoided fights and lies filled. Now it was only the weekend. Another night of no sleep and voices he shivered wishing that voice would show itself he was tired of his mother thinking that he was having wet dreams.<br />
"<br />
" &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;“Kiye..” h felt a shiver cores though him. “Kiyel” the whisper was close. At the end of his bed even. He pried into the darkness at the lone foggy outline of something, not quiet there yet. “I know you can hear me Kiyel, why won’t you answer? I feel lonely now Kiyel. I don’t like being lonely.” The room seemed to chill curtains over the closed window fluttering in the whispered air. “Who…” he gulped “who are you? Why are you here? Wha-“ his voice cracked. “ what do you want?” he felt the room change the curtains where laughing at him for the stupidity. The mirror on the wall was glaring angrily at the young man in bed whose face was pail and streaked with eyeliner and sweat. “No me Kilye.. no no” it laughed sadistically “ it is not me whom you should fear Kilye it is them.” &nbsp;The room was closing in.. The air was thinning; his breath came in ragged gulps as the darkness spun with stares and dazzling allusions of melting solids. “wh-“ he coughed <br />
"y“ who must I fear? Who?” his whispered please were greeted my silences that pressed in on him from all sides.<br />
"N“ answer &nbsp;me!” he shook with silent fear and rage. This thing had been with him for a good few months and it dare fird on his fears and kept him up at nights? No he would not deal with it. “come now .. you have the balls you keep me awake with you insistene whispers . feed upon my disheveled state of mind now answer me!”<br />
"fThe shadow ripped form its previous spot and rushed at his face causing a startled yelp and thump as he fell from his sitting position to the pillow staring the darkness in the fear . His room mocking him , laughing at his fear. “ watch your tongue boy.” It whispered. “ I came for your safety… but if you wish such ill will apon your deliverer…” &nbsp;it paused to let this sink in “ I shall leave you to them. My your body belong gone before the final blow.” &nbsp;With that the darkness shrank bake to normal as the room silenced to its normal self, the gaping window pains with there mocking mouths slipped back into sloth cool glass and the heat kicked on the back gound as he lay there. Panting , trying to get over this new bit of knowledge. “ so it will not bothered me again” he whispered as his shock and faer passed him into a deep and dreamless sleep.<br />
"<br />
"N &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; The world was hunting him now.<br />
"Mail boxes growled and snapped as he passed. Tree though there branches down upon his fragile head. Radios blaed defining him. Stones and crake found ther wawy into his path tripping him wherever he wint. And with every passing day it only got worse. Loneliness plagued his nights and vision he saw only the black and white as the colors mixed and formed into whirled of hatred and death threats panted themselves out of the food he ate. “are these the ones it was talking about?” he’d question himself daily pushing aside his food for lake of hunger as even his body was against him . Refusing sleep and light. Nightly he was plagued by visions of his own death. The times blurred and school stopped all together. His mother complained her boyfriend agreed like a puppy. It was all sickening to him, and it wouldn’t stop. No voices hade plagued him but every other night the world would gather and point and laugh as he lay petrified of his own shadow which took the shape of its own will and pointed at him &nbsp;mockingly. “is this,” he thought, “ what hell is like? It must be for nothing can be as bad as this.” And again he lived on as the bird glared at him from glassy eyes and midnight taunted him with the twelve tooling bells that ringed of laughter at his plight <br />
"<br />
"Ÿ &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;The voice returned after months of tormintion and the world stopped mocking him in its arrival. <br />
"y“ hello again Kiely” &nbsp;it whispered sharp more definition against the darkness. “and how are we tonight?”<br />
"ähe stared determining at the ceiling fan which whispered in its passing blades winging to answer the voice. He focused on disobeying it. “ &nbsp;oh now Kiley don’t be like that..” &nbsp;it purred movingly the room laughed<br />
