"7Title: Dearest Lover by MissGuideMe at All poetry
"
"	Dearest Lover,<br />
"XI can sense your eyes flickering in the light, adjusting to the nicorette scented mist, as shadows sway around you and Romeo's seranade their Juliets...Base beaths, dead heat, like a steady on going mantra of seduction. Without saying a word, your arms engulf me and the ashes of your burnt out cigarette float to the floor, resting on my toes as our legs snake around eachother... turn the timer sweetie and keep the sand moving... and I'll give you two minutes of my time. Street lights, cablights, thats what I'l do to you in the morning. Broken glasses, shattered vases, smudged mascara, and in our heated moment, you'll tell me I'm yours and I'll tell you your mine... but we but know thats not true... Pink skies, blue martinis, and red manhattans, lipstick is applied, and phone calls are made... Kiss you on the head sweetie, its time to go.<br />
"JHello,Goodmorning, We'll wait till next time... But for now lover...
"End of Poem
".Title: Joel by MissGuideMe at All poetry
"
"u	I used to be so good at speaking. I used to be so good at being able to share my thoughts. But without you, I can't speak anymore. Im searching for some kind of metaphor, some kind of artistically structured prose to explain you, to explain me. But its impossible, and you're impossible. I hate you for what you've done. I hate you for what you've made me become. I feel like I've gone backwards in time, to a time when life didnt make sense 2 me, to a time where an ever changing array of faces kept me from being lonely. But this time, the random faces make me more lonely, because they're not you. I thought i knew you so well, i thought we were the most perfect thing in the world. you helped me through some of the most challenging times in my life. you were ultimately the rock that got me 2 where i am 2day. I owe my success 2 you, because u loved me and made me believe i could do anything, and u gave me a reason 2 try. but you've turned ur back on me, and i feel like i almost couldnt forgive you. but you know id forgive you in a second. i was almost convinced you'd come back 2 me. but all hope of that is gone now. and i hate you for this. i truly hate you for burning our friendship 2 the ground, and it absolutely kills me that u cant face me anymore, and it makes me so angry that i cant just move on. like you have. ive thought about writing u a letter, but i think ive written 2 many of those, im almost afraid ud hate me if i did. ud think im being petty n immature, and disgusted i havent moved on. But i cant help it. because i dont hate you. i dont hate you at all. i love you. i love you so much it hurts, and it hurts that i cant get over you. im trying, i really am. but its not working. i wish i could hold u again, and tell you i love you. and to hear you say it back. Because i love you baby. and i always will. u may think i was a mistake. but my biggest mistake was losing you.
"End of Poem
"hTitle: A Bills of Rights Belonging To A Suicidal Teengage Republician by MissGuideMe at All poetry
"
"5	Sick of falling into this constant trap,<br />
"<br />
"<so i release my grip and let myself be violated,<br />
"<br />
"Violated. <br />
"<br />
"GMy rights are abused, infringed upon by the ageing society,<br />
"<br />
"mwho try to tell me that life was politically manageable in the days of monarchists and fascists. <br />
"<br />
"zPolitically manageable by force, politically influential by totalitarian extremists with blood tainted steel. <br />
"<br />
"tBut uncontrollable were the forces of the heart, beating like a time bomb that would eventually explode.<br />
"<br />
"Explode<br />
"<br />
"FSo into a new era we emerge, the youth of the ST century. <br />
"<br />
"YTired of being ridiculed by these ex bureaucrats who blame us for terrorism, <br />
"<br />
"JWho blame us for the rampant mismanagement of the environment,<br />
"<br />
"aAnd for the finances that overwhelm Wall Street and amaze the 42nd street financiers.<br />
"<br />
"DBut this youth has more important things to worry about.<br />
"<br />
"KPoetic letters of blackened injustice ridicule the constitution<br />
"<br />
"Ridicule <br />
"<br />
"JAs these quiescent teenagers silently cry out their injustice <br />
"<br />
"IWe realise we need to curb these half hearted suicidal notes,<br />
"<br />
"cThat often silently and inevitable become whole hearted suicidal notes of the deceased <br />
"<br />
"Deceased<br />
"<br />
"6So we decide to make a new bill of rights,<br />
"<br />
"-Assented by the youth themselves,<br />
"<br />
"DAnd passed by the present and future youth of the world,<br />
"<br />
"jTo aid our body count and provide relevant justice for those who crave republican domesticity <br />
"<br />
"OBut mostly to satisfy our own need of protection and satisfaction. <br />
"<br />
"0So to the youth of today we propose:<br />
"<br />
"b* We reserve the right to be notified of family changes which may affect our happiness<br />
"<br />
"[* We &nbsp;reserve the right to be notified when relationships are turning sour<br />
"<br />
"[* We reserve the right to be protected from breakups which affect our existence<br />
"<br />
"f* We acknowledge that NO ONE has the right to hurt us or make us feel like we don't belong<br />
"<br />
"^* We acknowledge that we dont have the right to be the one who is excluding others<br />
"<br />
"G* We acknowledge that alcohol wont forever reduce our tears<br />
"<br />
"O* We acknowledge that mystical substances aren't always the answer <br />
"<br />
"P* We want to be acknowledged, regardless of our intellectual ability<br />
"<br />
"<* We want to be heard, listened to, and accepted<br />
"<br />
"n* We want a world where we can truly express ourselves, without the fear of rejection or exclusion<br />
"<br />
"T* We want protection from rejection, and right to immediate acceptance. <br />
"<br />
"x*We reserve the right to ask for help and receive it when needed, no matter what the time, or the situation <br />
"<br />
"D*And finally, we reserve the right to be loved. always. <br />
"<br />
"Right <br />
"<br />
"½This forms the convention of the modern teenage republicans who care about who they are, and what they can be.....this is to be passed to ensure the survival of the teens of today...<br />
"<br />
"End of Poem
"QTitle: Emo eyes and half hearted suicide notes by MissGuideMe at All poetry
"
"?	The swirling black water engulfing my tired body, <br />
"Gthe current is sweeping away my tears and freezing my mind,<br />
"Iim sick of your artificial fallacies and heart shaped kisses,<br />
"TA bleeding guitar pick acts as a reminder of the songs you used to sing,<br />
"Kstrings stained red remind us of the jerking of our own hearts.<br />
"?Blackness symbolising the mutual feelings now gone,<br />
"(the salinity now chokes me, <br />
"5my body bathed in my own tears of regret.<br />
":Symphony orchestras playing in the background,<br />
"1stare back at me with their emo eyes,<br />
"?the treble which tells the story of our own demise.<br />
"DI never asked to be a part of your satanic complications<br />
"YI never asked to be the reason for your association's result in self torment.<br />
"8Mistaken perspections, regretting acceptance<br />
"@I didn't want to be a part of your self manipulation<br />
"'all i wanted was your love,<br />
"Ninstead i recieved decayed reasons and half hearted suicide notes,<br />
"<and i've lost a part of me i can never get back.<br />
"FLike pieces of a mosaic, there's no place for you anymore,<br />
"*not in my mascara laden heart.<br />
"<You'll no longer belong to my rose tinted world,<br />
"Aonly forced to bear your own dissolusioned happiness.<br />
"EWater engulfing me, the salinity sears back up my throat,<br />
" I can breathe again,<br />
"DAnd the orchestra completes their finale....to silence. <br />
